      "para_id": "Q000835.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) Enheduana , the zirru - priestess , Nanna's spouse , child of Šarrukin , king of the world , erected an altar in the temple of Inana-ZAZA in Urim . She named it “The altar is An's table” ."
